To install the perl modules using MCPAN 

perl -MCPAN -e 'install Gtk2'


For all some important modules.
libxml-*-perl



to list out the modules which are installed + select a module

use this "instmodsh" command 


this command will show only the module names
apt-cache search tree | grep perl | awk -v x=1 '{print $1}' > file 

then do sed ':a;N;$!ba;s/\n/ /g' file 
it will show all the modules name in the terminal so select them and run 


sudo apt-get install <modules name> 
